## Sidebar Connections View Filtering

Filter the Connections tab in the sidebar to show only adapters and agents relevant to the currently selected agent.

### FSD Layer Consideration

The `NavigationLayout` lives in `shared/ui/` and cannot import from `entities` or `features`. The filtering data must be provided by the parent component via props.

### NavigationLayout Props

In `apps/client/src/layers/shared/ui/navigation-layout.tsx`, add an optional `connectionFilter` prop:

```typescript
interface NavigationLayoutProps {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  // NEW
  connectionFilter?: {
    agentName: string;
    filteredAdapterIds: string[];
    totalAdapterCount: number;
    onClearFilter: () => void;
  };
}
```

### Filtering UI

Inside the Connections tab content in `NavigationLayout`, apply the filter:

```tsx
{connectionFilter && (
  <div className="flex items-center justify-between px-3 py-1.5 text-xs text-muted-foreground">
    <span>
      Showing {connectionFilter.filteredAdapterIds.length} of{' '}
      {connectionFilter.totalAdapterCount} adapters for{' '}
      <span className="font-medium text-foreground">
        {connectionFilter.agentName}
      </span>
    </span>
    <Button
      variant="link"
      size="sm"
      className="h-auto p-0 text-xs"
      onClick={connectionFilter.onClearFilter}
    >
      Show all
    </Button>
  </div>
)}
```

When `connectionFilter` is provided, filter the adapter list to only show adapters whose IDs are in `filteredAdapterIds`.

### Parent Component Integration

In the parent that renders `NavigationLayout` (likely in `features/settings/` or `widgets/`), compute the filter:

```typescript
import { useBindings } from '@/layers/entities/binding';
import { useRegisteredAgents } from '@/layers/entities/mesh';
import { useAdapterCatalog } from '@/layers/entities/relay';

function useConnectionFilter(currentAgentId: string | undefined) {
  const { data: bindings = [] } = useBindings();
  const { data: catalog = [] } = useAdapterCatalog();
  const [filterEnabled, setFilterEnabled] = useState(true);

  if (!currentAgentId || !filterEnabled) return undefined;

  const agentBindings = bindings.filter(b => b.agentId === currentAgentId);
  const filteredAdapterIds = [...new Set(agentBindings.map(b => b.adapterId))];
  const totalAdapterCount = catalog.reduce((sum, entry) => sum + entry.instances.length, 0);

  // Get agent name from bindings or agents
  const agentName = currentAgentId; // Resolve from mesh if needed

  return {
    agentName,
    filteredAdapterIds,
    totalAdapterCount,
    onClearFilter: () => setFilterEnabled(false),
  };
}
```

Pass the result as `connectionFilter` prop to `NavigationLayout`.

Determining the current agent: check the Zustand store or URL params (`?session=`) to identify the active session's agent. If no agent is selected, return undefined (no filter applied).

